            . I live in <placeName id="t18300415-270-crimeloc1491">Margaret-street, Hackney-fields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-270-crimeloc1491" type="placeName" value="Margaret-street, Hackney-fields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-270-crimeloc1491" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-270-off1489 t18300415-270-crimeloc1491"></join>. I was in my kitchen in the afternoon, on the 2nd of April - I went into my shop, and saw the prisoner at the counter; he asked for a halfpenny worth of sugar - I asked if he had no more money, he said No; I said I would make him a half-penny worth; I took some paper to put it in, and missed my weights; I said."Where are my weights?" he said,</p>
               <p>"I will go and get more money" - he ran out, I pursued him; he was stopped and brought back in ten minutes; the weights were found in the middle of the road; three were found exactly corresponding with those I lost.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-270-person2332">
                  FRANCIS 
                  CLARK
               <interp inst="t18300415-270-person2332" type="surname" value="CLARK"></interp>
